weather.description: Looking like around 20mph sustained winds in TB, with gusts around 30. Deeper passes and long FG's could be a bit of an issue. Showers are also possible, but like Jax I don't expect the rain to be particularly heavy or long-lived (if they see any at all).

SoFi Stadium is (as I understand it) an open air but roofed stadium. So the rain is not an issue, but it will be a breezy day, so the question is how much does wind matter? I'm assuming the answer to that is "not very much".
Wind around 15-20mph, gusting close to 30. A few deeper passes and kicks impacted (sticking with YLW here, but kind of on the fence about making it ORNG).
Chance for rain, but nothing too heavy or prolonged (mostly dry),  winds a bit over 15mph sustained with stronger gusts.
